Alternative to Louvain : Leiden and Surprise¶

In [23]:
from cdlib import algorithms
#Surprise, Leiden

G_i = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, label_attribute='original_name')
mapping = {old_label:new_label for new_label, old_label in enumerate(G.nodes())}
inv_mapping = {v: k for k, v in mapping.items()}

leid = algorithms.leiden(G_i)
supr = algorithms.surprise_communities(G_i)

leid_com = leid.communities
supr_com = supr.communities

Note: to be able to use all crisp methods, you need to install some additional packages:  {'karateclub', 'infomap', 'graph_tool'}
Note: to be able to use all overlapping methods, you need to install some additional packages:  {'karateclub', 'ASLPAw'}
Note: to be able to use all bipartite methods, you need to install some additional packages:  {'infomap'}

We will focus on cells linking the adaptive and innate immune cells i.e "APC" eg. macrophage, dentritic cells

node_interest = ["Macrophage", "DC", "TNFa", "IL6"]
louv_dict = {}
for i in range(100):
    louv_i = community_louvain.best_partition(G_1)
    for p in node_interest:
        if p not in louv_dict:
            louv_dict[p] = [louv_i[p]]
        else:
            louv_dict[p].append(louv_i[p])

In [298]:
leid_dict = {}
num_interest = [mapping["Macrophage"], mapping["DC"], mapping["TNFa"], mapping["IL6"]]

for i in range(100):
    leid_com_i = algorithms.leiden(G_i).communities
    a = -1 
    for com in leid_com_i:
        a += 1
        for p in num_interest:
            if p in com:
                if p  not in leid_dict:
                    leid_dict[p] = [a]
                    
                if p in leid_dict:
                    leid_dict[p].append(a)

        if path_l <= 3:
            e = (n1, n2)
            simple_edge.append(e)
    except:
        pass
